<doc id="262179" wikidata="Q7143676" url="?curid=262179" title="Pat Lowther Award">
<text>The Pat Lowther Memorial Award is an annual Canadian literary award presented by the League of Canadian Poets to the year&#x27;s best book of poetry by a Canadian woman. The award was established in 1980 to honour poet Pat Lowther, who was murdered by her husband in 1975. Each winner receives an honorarium of $1000.

