<doc id="262204" wikidata="Q969024" url="?curid=262204" title="Gerald Lampert Award">
<text>The Gerald Lampert Memorial Award is an annual literary award presented by the League of Canadian Poets to the best volume of poetry published by a first-time poet. It is presented in honour of poetry promoter Gerald Lampert. Each winner receives an honorarium of $1000.

In its earliest years, the award was not necessarily limited to poetry, but was presented to the year&#x27;s best first book by a Canadian writer in either poetry or prose.

