<doc id="262222" wikidata="Q13108171" url="?curid=262222" title="Aramidae">
<text>Aramidae is a bird family in the order Gruiformes. The limpkin (&quot;Aramus guarauna&quot;) is the only living member of this family, although other species are known from the fossil record, such as &quot;Aramus paludigrus&quot; from the Middle Miocene and &quot;Badistornis aramus&quot; from Oligocene.

